  "texts": [
    "By identifying named entities consistently across languages, tasks such as cross-lingual information retrieval, crosslingual summarization, or knowledge graph alignment can be better performed.",
    "In summary, NER in resource-poor languages is essential for enabling language understanding [11], [19], [20], [23], [25], [26].Based on Information retrieval systems require the contextual data that surrounds NEs where names perform an important role in information retrieval as significant information is always surrounded by NEs [27], [28].",
    "Names have traditionally subscribed to the belief that automatic text summarization [29], biomedical data and text summarization systems can effectively use investigated NEs as they remain intact in all languages [4], [30], [31] NER models are typically trained using supervised machine learning techniques, where annotated training data is used to teach the model to recognize and classify named entities.",
    "These models employ various linguistic features, such as part-of-speech tags, word context, and syntactic information, to make predictions about the entities present in the text.",
